<div id="c5">
<p>Good rant. I think what Aaron is saying isn&#8217;t that these sites are not helpful, but that &#8220;the generous impulses behind transparency sites end up doing more harm than good.&#8221;</p>

<p>So, it&#8217;s the exuberance behind &#8220;transparency-for-its-own-sake&#8221; that he takes issue with. I&#8217;m sure he agrees with all the comments saying transparency is fine as part of a larger movement; I think he just wants to make sure people have the correct expectations of what transparency alone is (and isn&#8217;t) capable of.</p>

